entries.femaleVariant: Found Bartmoss' deck.
Hey, Nix, listen. Found something... Bartmoss' deck.
Mhm. What else'd ya find? Alan Turing's tapes?
Think you can pull anything off it?
Mm… Tech's comin' apart, humidity damaged... Encryption on the memcube – gotta be near divine.
Fine. Get to it.
Best let it be.
Ya know what…? We should let it lie.
No risk, no reward. Get to it.
I getcha. But should you change your mind… I be waitin' right here.
"All yours?" Oh, V, V… got no sense of reverence... Expect if you found the goddamn Holy Grail, you'd fill it with caramel corn and Pop-Turds...
Now, let's get this show underway. Hm, hm. Most data's corrupt… but not all. Password? A dictattack, maybe...? Nothin' doin'. And what about injectin' a command…?
All yours.
Think the disk might be infected?
Think there could be some no longer known vectors on the disk? A DataKrash-like thing or RABIDs? 'Cause if so…
Hah! Gotcha!
Spare me the two-step. Yes, or no?
I can try. Failure, though, is a distinct possibility. Then all data'll be lost, done and gone.
Changed my mind. Give it a shot.
Thought about it... Let's give it a shot.
entries.maleVariant: Uh, thought about it... Let's give it a shot.

entries.femaleVariant: Bein' serious. Have a look-see.
Now get the fuck outta my face, dawg.
Ooooh, runnin' shits. God damn, V!
Where'd ya ferret this out of?
Found it in a fridge.
Not your biz.
Found it outside town. In a fridge... next to its former owner's rotting corpse.
Hmph. Bartmoss all the way. NetWatch made him a wanted man, went lookin' in Shanghai, Lahore, Santiago de Chile…
While that dawg alighted to the Net. Wonder how long he'da kept buzzin' those wires if the power hadn't gone out.
Found it under my Christmas tree.
Mhm. But serious, like?
Serious, like, it's just not your biz.
OK. Put the deck on the counter... just ginger-like!
Then we pop open a bottle of malignant gin.
Painfully aware of the risks, I am. But speakin' straight… curiosity's consumin' me. You feel it, too?
Hah! We're golden. One more hurdle, but it oughta be as easy as pie. My, my, of all people, Bartmoss shoulda done better.
Aaargh! Argh! Aaaaarrrghhh!
Dog shit, cat shit, rat shit…
Ideas, V, fast and stat. Couple of minutes and his skull sponge'll be well-done steak.
Reset this baby.
Of course, fuck!
Goddammit!
OOO-K... Can't be that difficult, can it?
entries.maleVariant: 'Kay... Can't be that difficult, can it?

entries.femaleVariant: OK, whadda we got here…?
Simp, sure. Deck only belonged to the twenty-first century's most superb hacker.
Wanna do this? No? Then shut your pipe.
Saw what we got – a brain broiler. You absolutely sure you wanna jack in?
Tssshhhh.
Aaa… Errgh… fuck a muffin…
You breathin'?
Apparently... though it feels like I got a skull full o' hot embers.
Just... what the hell happened?
So I sat down and finished for you.
entries.maleVariant: So I sat down and finished for ya.

entries.femaleVariant: So I killed the power. It helped.
You started convulsing, lights went out, outlets started spittin' sparks…
Hold up, hold up… Mean to say you breached Bartmoss' deck? Lowly you?
Shiiit, wait, the deck... Oh, man. It's wiped. All gone.
Rather have died?
Could be for the best.
Yep. Know the net inside out.
Got lucky.
Guess I got a little lucky.
Damn straight. I'm the best netrunner in town, after all.
entries.maleVariant: Damn straight. I am the best netrunner in town, after all.

entries.femaleVariant: Rather have died? Really?
Prolly better this way. Can't know what was on there. Mighta been nasty, brought the net down again.
A'ight... Let's see just what you pulled from this artefact…
Listen, my services usually command a tidy sum. But this time, well… seems you rendered me a service.
Doubt it, kid. Buuut… maybe someday.
Had luck comin' out your ears, kid.
Logs... mail... chat history o' sorts... Hm. Potentially interestin', but nothin' explosive.
Ah, shame, kinda. Well, guess I can delve some more, see if I can't find somethin' interesting in there.
entries.maleVariant: Shame, kinda. Well, I guess I can delve some more, see if I can't find somethin' interesting in there.

entries.femaleVariant: No, 'course not, but... Shit, now I'm 'onna spend the rest of my life wonderin' what was on there.
Ya know... find myself wonderin'... what the world'd be like if we suddenly found ourselves back in the age of telephones... or the telegraph. If it wouldn't just be better.
Take this. Handful of daemons live on that shard. Wasn't Bartmoss who coded 'em... but they should be useful nonetheless.
Thanks, Nix... Ya gonna get it together, be all right? Or you need help?
No, no, be just fine. Couple o' painkillers washed down with whiskey, and I'll be a new man.
[Set down deck]
[Show deck] Take a look.
